dc_description_s: "Base map compiled in 1980 by Soil Conservation Service ... from USGS 1:24 000 scale topographic maps dated 1953-1963".; "Interpretations derived from soil map constructed 1963 by Cartographic Division, Soil Conservation Service, USDA, of York County, Pennsylvania".; Includes location map and notes.; Shows "prime farmland", "additional farmland of statewide importance", "unique farmland", "other land", "water areas", "land subject to controlled inundation," and "approximate urban and built-up areas".|114 x 182 centimeters, sheets 123 x 102 centimeters. +|Scale 1:50,000
